ral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/27/5" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2007.27.issue-5/asset/14a16856-2614-1685-0261-a1685602614a/radiographics.2007.27.issue-5.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">27</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">5</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Sep 1 2007</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">1389</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1400</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17848698/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">17848698</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2007.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Sep 1 2007</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.275065163">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=APACHE+II+%3D+Acute+Physiology+and+Chronic+Health+Evaluation+II&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">APACHE II = Acute Physiology and Chronic Health Evaluation II</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ERCP+%3D+endoscopic+retrograde+cholangiopancreatography&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ERCP = endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">In disconnection of the pancreatic duct, which occurs in the setting of severe acute pancreatitis, a viable segment of the pancreatic body or tail is isolated from the gastrointestinal tract; the imaging features of this entity are discussed, as well as diagnostic pitfalls and treatment options.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Kumaresan</span> <span property="familyName">Sandrasegaran</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Radiology (K.S., M.T., S.G.J., D.D.M.), Surgery (S.D.P., T.J.H.), and Medicine (S.S.), Indiana University School of Medicine, 550 N University Blvd, Suite UH 0279, Indianapolis, IN 46202. Recipient of a Certificate of Merit award for an education exhibit at the 2005 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received September 5, 2006; revision requested October 30 and received December 18; accepted December 19. K.S. receives research support from Koninklijke Philips Electronics NV, Cleveland, Ohio; D.D.M. is a consultant for Cook, Bloomington, Ind, and E-Z-Em, Westburg, NY; S.S. is a consultant for Repligen, Waltham, Mass; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Sandrasegaran/Kumaresan" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Mark</span> <span property="familyName">Tann</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Radiology (K.S., M.T., S.G.J., D.D.M.), Surgery (S.D.P., T.J.H.), and Medicin